description: The harried armies of the Eastern Kingdoms are granted a brief respite as the forces of the Demon Lord Astaroth, and those of the Dataran Invasion force, clash together at the mouth of Mount Eganko. Confused by the seemingly inexplicable dissension among their enemies, our heroes beat a hasty retreat towards the Vantish border in the hopes that they can organize some manner of defense while finding an ally in the most unexpected place imaginable.
name: Dragon's Peace
I sette nani e il cristallo di re Arbor

description: The Darklyte armor is almost within Aalok's grasp, but the armor itself is not without its protection. It's up to our heroes to reach the armor before Aalok and his cohorts can defeat the armor's mysterious guardian. Meanwhile, the Elves of Yattannia come in full force to the aid their new allies, but with Aalok so close to his goal and the already daunting presence of the Dataran Horde, can our heroes possibly hope to turn back the tide of battle?
name: Fallen Comrades
Topolino e gli enigmi del tempo
Zio Paperone e la vecchia pepita

description: Confused by his new found powers, Aalock journeys south towards the land of the dwarves in search of answers. Malagen however, has no intention of allowing Aalock to serve any other causes than that of his own. To that end Malagen sends the Vampire lord Vardemis to bring Aalock back pitting the two Vampire lords against each other in the most crucial battle of the Darklyte crusade to date! Meanwhile, the armies of the Eastern kingdoms regroup and prepare for a desperate all-out counter attack against the Dataran Horde in effort to save the lives of thousands of displaced refugees fleeing the front lines of battle. So sharpen your sword, don't bother taking off your armor, and jump right back in as Dreamwave productions brings you WARLANDS #8.
name: Fallen Comrades
Topolino e la corsa del secolo
Topolino e il mostro del lago

description: The final battle that will decide the fate of Warlands begins as the haggard armies of the eastern kingdoms consider their options after suffering a crushing defeat at the mouth of Dragon's Peace. No one could have predicted the strange, and unlikely new ally that would come to join them, or the desperate strategy that he would offer them. Pitted against an overwhelming superior army, our heroes must journey alone behind enemy lines to take on the Vampire Lords themselves! So tend to your wounds and try keep up with the rest of us as Dreamwave Productions bring you Warlands Chaper #9.
name: Aalok's Reckoning

description: After fighting a losing battle since the onset of the war, the balance of power may have finally shifted in our heroes' favor. Aalok, high prince of Datara has unexpectedly switched sides, and has agreed to fight back against his former masters. In possession of the Darklyte armor, can Aalok overcome his dark heritage? Will our heroes be able to trust their strange new ally? Polish your swords and get ready for the counter-attack in this special jump-on issue of Warlands. Also in this issue: Shidima Prequel! Featured on the flipside of Warlands #10 is the Shidima Prequel featuring an exclusive, full color 8 page sequential story from Dreamwave's newest ongoing series. The Shidima Prequel will be the first published offering of Shidima, and will only be available in Warlands #10.
name: Vampire's Reckoning

description: As the Eastern Kingdoms and the Vampires and Orcs of the Dataran Horde clash in a final battle for control of Warlands, King Atrelegis, former ruler of the Eastern Kingdom of Myridorn, and until recently, a vampire within the ranks of the Horde himself, must fight a desperate battle against Malagen the Black, Kahn of Datara. But can our heroes hold back the rush of the Datarans long enough for Atrelegis to maneuver Malagen into a direct confrontation? Can Atrelegis overcome his dark heritage and learn the secrets of the Darklyte Armor in time to defeat Malagen?
name: Into the Teeth of Darkness

description: The Darklyte crusade nears it's conclusion. Malagen and his vampire hordes have pushed the armies of the Eastern kingdoms to the brink of defeat. Our heroes have one final hope. On the flaming ruins of the battlefield, King Atrelegis, wielder of the legendary Darklyte armor, and formerly a vampire in Malagen's army himself, confronts his dark heritage and challenges Malagen to a battle that will decide the fate of an entire world! Meanwhile, G'Dar ventures off alone against the demon lord Astaroth, to avenge the death of his brother.
name: Reckoning

description: Greyson begins to question the wisdom of joining Belmiro as their plans begin to unravel amidst a vampiric civil war. But how much is Greyson willing to risk in his quest to regain his humanity? Now that Belmiro's enemies are his own, bowing out of a partnership with the cunning vampire will be more difficult than either vampire could have imagined.

Alex London isn't helping Razor's state of mind when he dumps the drugs she uses to keep her self relatively sane. But in her current jittery state he can still over power her telling her he wants a level head on her when the take the fight to Von Drake.

Von Drake himself is training to keep himself ready for any encounter that might be coming. Stryke is becoming increasingly unhappy. He nearly got her killed when he had her fight to prove her supremacy as his top assassin and ever since she fought Razor she has been having childhood dreams that confuse her with another little girl and her dead father in them. She suspects Von Drake is holding back information about her past and is increasingly anxious to know what it is.

Meanwhile Razor is sure that Styke is her sister despite a body being identified as her sister being found 2 months after her abduction when they were children.

Von Drake review the tape of his clash with Razor, fully aware of who she is and why shes coming after him. His 10am meeting is the the chief of police. He shows him the tape of London rescuing razor and states he wants him dead.

Razor takes Alex to Cat's as she re-equips herself for combat with anew suit, grenades and blades.

Bonus Preview Story: Achilles Storm

The regular story is broken for this issue while Hartsoe hands off some of the work while he dedicates his time to the 'The Suffering' mini series.  
 
Razor remembers an early victim of crime, Julie Ann who was raped and killed in a park, that she so nearly managed to save. 
 
Razor saves a would be rape victim on the underground.
name: First Steps; Dark Reflections

description:
Stryke is sent on a mission to educate local brothers whose smuggling operation is owned by Von Drake but are looking to challenge him as leader of Queen Cities crime lords. They have also been holding out on money they owe him.

Most of th thug go down easily before the nearly naked and ultra violent Stryke. Only twin sisters, the last line of the brothers defense, give her any trouble... and then not much at that. She kills two hidden gunmen and as final warning slays one of the brothers.

She returns to Von Drake and they make love.

Bonus Preview Story: The Suffering
name: Warning

description:
Razor confronts Von Drake and gets in a few cuts before he take the upper hand. Stryke is badly hurt but piecing together her family history with a growing anger towards Von Drakes lies. 
 
Drake takes a gun to Strykes head and Razor puts a blade through his chest.. but still he lives. He tell the girls he loved their mother and she refused him for her husband. But the one night they had together.. he claims Nicole was the result and he is her father. 
 
Razor thinks back to that night.. and the last words she hers Drake say confirm that he is her father. they fight and just as he is about to kill Razor, Stryke shoots him through the head. 
 
Even though she fulfilled her destiny, Razor still says that it hurts inside. 
 
Elsewhere, Alex London is drawing his last breaths in hospital. 
 
Bonus Preview Story: Demonique
name: Finale

description:
Alex London is dead and Razor ribs a criminal for money to fly out to New York for a new start. Even in a new town she finds her dreams full of the tortured memories of her brutal existence and laments that Von Drake didn't kill her. 
 
Prologue 
A couple in a night club meet a devastatingly beautiful woman and when they leave she and thuggish friends kill the man and take the woman. 
 
Six years prior in South East Asia Stryke has finishes he training and daggers are pained all over her naked body. She enters a compound filled with heavily armed and battle ready men. She kills silently and uses only her hands and their own weapons. She takes out the last man but is shot through the shoulder.
name: Beginnings; Ice...

description:
Nicole tries to suppress her violent alter-ego Razor in a battle for her own sanity. Since Von Drakes death her temper has been somewhat quietened and resisting drugs is actually getting easier now she doesn't have her rage to contend with.

Even so she still faints at work and while taking a walk in the park with a co-worker she sees man being attacked and Razor takes over.

One evening a loud man, Brock, gropes her ass and she is saved by a male member of staff before she can hurt him. Later that night as they lock up a woman pulls a gun on Nicole and her friend ordering them into her car. They shoot her friend and Nicole makes her escape with blood on her hands. They woman and her thugs hunt her down and Razor emerges and kills every one of them, dispatching Brock with a spectacular flip, kick and 2 shots to the chest all in one move.

Razor is back.
name: Rituals, Part 1 of 2

description:
Razor visits her friend in hospital while a long haired assassin lays waste to a crime syndicate. The last member of the syndicate asks her why razor is doing this to them. She yanks off the wig and reveals herself to be Stryke and shes been hired by their former boss. 
 
Back in Queen city  Nicole drops in on Kat and rearms herself as Razor, ready to start her one woman war on crime again.
name: Rituals, 2 of 2

description: After a harrowing battle for survival in the blood stained halls of Tessan's Abbey, Greyson finds himself face to face with Tessan, vampire lord of Datara. With victory comes the promise of eternal life, or death at peace as mortal. But to seal that victory, Greyson must dins a way to defeat Tessan, while holding at bat an entire army of vampires at the same time.
Razor takes on the werewolf menace but gets in over her head and needs some help from Silas Payne before she meets her end.

Collecting all of the previous appearances of fan-favorite Brian Bolland's humorous, yet provocative and slightly potentially offensive (for the politically correct-minded) tales of everyone's favorite Bishop and his actress mistress. A must for any fan of Brian Bolland's sharp wit and elegant line work!
The battle with Attila heats up...and Katar could well turn out to be a casualty of their war.
name: Kill The Guilty!

description: The government of Thanagar has sanctioned the theft of a revolutionary space drive, but its owner has sicked the deadly intergalactic bounty hunter Smif'beau after the thieves...and Smif'beau is willing to kill everyone to finish his mission.
name: Sirius Matters
